There is no pressure.
Only invitation.
Final Word to the Elders
You are not late.
You are not irrelevant.
You are not finished.
You are the bridge between what was survived
and what does not need to be repeated.
Stand where you are.
Speak what you know.
Offer the map — even if they don’t follow it immediately.
Seeds planted in truth grow quietly.
And history remembers those who chose to pass the torch
instead of watching the fire go out.

